  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the efficacy of a SSRI,
      cognitive-bahavioral-therapy and a free choice between SSRI and CBT in a sample of primary
      care patients suffering from mild to moderate depression.

      Hypotheses:

        -  SSRI is superior to placebo

        -  CBT is superior to a non-specific supporting group therapy
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
